\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 The aghori continued: \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93and I don\u8217\'92t want mutton or chicken. I want human flesh.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 Sagal shah, resigned to his fate, said \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93all right, maharaj, I will have myself killed and cooked and served to you.\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 This only made the aghori wilder. \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93Dunce! You are an old man. Think how stringy and tough your meat will be. I want a young child. Take his brains and fry them for me.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 Sagal shah said, \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93I have a young son who is in school right now. I will go and bring him and have his brains cooked for you.\u8221\'94 His wife, who was pregnant, also realized that it had to be done, to fulfill the vow.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 Sagal shah went and found chelayya, his son, and asked him to come home with him. Before he could explain why, chelayya told him, \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93so that old fellow wants to fry my brains and eat them? All right, let us go there and I will see how he does it.\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 His father should have suspected something when chelayya knew all about the aghori before being told. But sagal shah was too distraught over his son\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92s impending death to notice. How could chelayya know about it? He was something different; his own father had not realized who he was.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 They went to sagal shah\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92s house and chelayya told the aghori, \u8220\'93so you\u8217\'92re trying to be funny, eh? Allright, do it! Go ahead!\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 And he was slaughtered and his brains pulverized, and dish was prepared. The mortar and pestle in which his brains were mashed can still be seen on that island.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 When the meat was set before the aghori, he became wilder still and refused to eat it, saying, \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93how can you expect me to eat food prepared by a barren woman? Shameless wretch!\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 This was too much for sagal Shah\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92s wife, who said to him, \u8220\'93You damned aghori! Who do you think you are? I am pregnant, so you dare not call me barren. Now I am going to make you eat and I am going to watch and see how you do it!\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 Suddenly, the aghori said to the corpse of the boy, \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93Get up!\u8221\'94 and immediately the boy was standing there alive saying, \u8220\'93So?\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 Then the aghori instantly bowed to chelayya and said to sagal shah, \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93request a boon!\u8221\'94 Sagal shah replied, \u8220\'93Lord, what can I ask for? In kali Yuga no one is tested like this, and you have graced my by being born into my family. Now all that I can ask is that all in my family and all my descendants should have pure minds. Anyone who develops perverted intellect should be destroyed.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 And to it has been until today.}
